  "high_level_description": "A painterly watercolor illustration of a misty summer dawn at an ancient Alsatian watermill, with a weathered stone-and-wood mill and iron-bound undershot waterwheel beside a burbling stream, a grizzled hunter and wirehaired hound silhouetted in the forest behind, foxgloves framing the lower-left corner.",
  "compositional_deconstruction": {
    "background": "Misty summer dawn sky rendered as soft watercolor washes in pearl-gray tones with faint gold-tinged breaks where dawn light slips through high clouds. Dense mixed beech and oak forest looms behind the mill in deep shadow, shafts of cloudlight filtering through the canopy. A pale ribbon of low ground mist drifts across the gently burbling stream surface, which cuts diagonally from lower-left to mid-right past the waterwheel. Wet cobblestones edge into the foreground. Muted palette of slate gray, mossy green, weathered timber brown, and pale silver water, with localized warm light only where it breaks through the canopy. Painterly visible brushwork, soft edges, atmospheric depth, fine ink linework on structural elements.",
